Name: EventStatus
Title: EventStatus
Description: Codes identifying the lifecycle stage of an event.

Name: AfibFlutterStatusCS
Title: Atrial Fibrillation or Flutter Status Codes
Description: Codes representing the status of Atrial Fibrillation or Flutter assessment.

Name: AssessmentContextCS
Title: Assessment Context Code System
Description: Codes defining the context or timing of a clinical assessment, particularly functional scores.

Name: InitialCareIntensityCS
Title: Initial Care Intensity Code System
Description: Codes indicating the level of care provided during the patient's initial day(s) in the hospital.

Name: MRsScoreCS
Title: modified Rankin Scale (mRS) Score Code System
Description: Codes representing the modified Rankin Scale (mRS) score for functional outcome.

Name: MticiScoreCS
Title: mTICI Score Code System
Description: CodeSystem containing the codes to represent the mTICI score.

Name: ProcedureTimingContextCS
Title: Procedure Timing Context Code System
Description: Codes defining the timing phase of a procedure relative to the encounter start (e.g., acute vs. post-acute).

Name: StrokeArrivalModeCS
Title: Initial Care Intensity Code System
Description: Codes indicating the level of care provided during the patient's initial day(s) in the hospital.

Name: StrokeProcNotDoneReasonCS
Title: Stroke Procedure Not Done Reason Code System
Description: Codes specifying the reason principal for not performing a key stroke procedure (Thrombolysis, Thrombectomy).

Name: SwallowScreenTimeCS
Title: Swallowing Screening Timing Category Code System
Description: Temporal categories relative to stroke onset for swallowing screening.

Name: TimingMetricCodesCS
Title: Stroke Timing Metric Codes ValueSet
Description: Codes for key process timing metrics in acute stroke care (D2N, D2G).
